Gitlab CI/CD: 

 

[] Go to GitLab repo <> create a file name with .gitlab-ci.yml  in main branch 

[] Go to settings <>CI/CD<>runner<>gave tag name (whatever)<>create runner  

[] select the server type <> we will get command <> copy the command  

 
[] Go to the slave server. 
[] we have to install runners on the slave server.  
[] past the command.  
[] we will get connection success.  
 
[] in GitLab also we can see online.  
 
[] sample .gitlab-ci.yml 
# Define the order of stages 
stages: 
 - build 
 - test 
 - deploy 
 
# Define a job for the build stage 
build-job: 
 stage: build 
 script: 
   - echo "Compiling the code..." 
 
# Define a job for the test stage 
test-job: 
 stage: test 
 script: 
   - echo "Running unit tests..." 
 
# Define a job for the deploy stage 
deploy-job: 
 stage: deploy 
 script: 
   - echo "Deploying application to production..." 
 rules: 
   - if: $CI_COMMIT_BRANCH == $CI_DEFAULT_BRANCH # Only deploy from the main branch 
 

